(JavaScript Data Flow Guide For This Journal App) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Project references) Tj
T*
(- templates/page.html lines 103, 129, 144, 157, 165, 205, 226, 254, 295, 299) Tj
T*
(- journals/serializers.py) Tj
T*
(- journals/models.py) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Big picture) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The JavaScript in templates/page.html exists to connect three layers:) Tj
T*
(1\) the browser UI,) Tj
T*
(2\) the HTTP API,) Tj
T*
(3\) Django database saving.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The browser does not save journals to the database by itself. It only collects values from) Tj
T*
(the page and sends them to Django. Django and Django REST Framework validate the incoming) Tj
T*
(data and save it through the serializer and model.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The flow for saving is:) Tj
T*
(- The user types a title, picks a date, and writes content in Quill.) Tj
T*
(- saveData\(\) reads those values from the DOM.) Tj
T*
(- toIsoStringFromLocalInput\(\) converts the date input to a standard ISO string.) Tj
T*
(- JSON.stringify\(\) turns the JavaScript object into JSON text.) Tj
T*
(- fetch\('/api/journals/', { method: 'POST', ... }\) sends the request to Django.) Tj
T*
(- The serializer parses journal_date as a DateTimeField.) Tj
T*
(- The model stores the row in the database.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The flow for reading is:) Tj
T*
(- loadJournals\(\) sends a GET request to /api/journals/.) Tj
T*
(- Django returns only journals for the logged-in user.) Tj
T*
(- renderJournalList\(\) turns that response into clickable journal items.) Tj
T*
(- Clicking one item loads its values back into the editor.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Why JSON is used here) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(JSON is not the database. JSON is just the transport format used between JavaScript and) Tj
T*
(Django over HTTP.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Without JSON, the frontend would still need some format to send structured data like:) Tj
T*
(- journal_title) Tj
T*
(- journal_description) Tj
T*
(- journal_date) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(JSON is a good fit because:) Tj
T*
(- browsers work with JavaScript objects naturally,) Tj
T*
(- Django REST Framework parses JSON well,) Tj
T*
(- nested and structured data stays readable,) Tj
T*
(- it is the normal format for APIs.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(So the rule is:) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
