(- JavaScript creates an object,) Tj
T*
(- JSON carries that object over the network,) Tj
T*
(- Django saves it into models.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. Function by function explanation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(getCookie\(name\) in page.html line 103) Tj
T*
(Why it exists:) Tj
T*
(- Django protects POST and DELETE requests with CSRF.) Tj
T*
(- If the frontend sends data without the CSRF token, Django may reject the request.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How it works:) Tj
T*
(- It reads document.cookie.) Tj
T*
(- It finds the cookie named csrftoken.) Tj
T*
(- It returns the token so fetch\(\) can send it in the headers.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this matters for data:) Tj
T*
(- It is part of secure writing, not part of journal content itself.) Tj
T*
(- The save and delete requests depend on it.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(toDateTimeLocalValue\(dateValue\) in page.html line 129) Tj
T*
(Why it exists:) Tj
T*
(- A datetime-local input expects a local browser-style value like YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm.) Tj
T*
(- The API usually returns an ISO datetime.) Tj
T*
(- Those two formats are related but not identical in usage.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How it works:) Tj
T*
(- It builds a Date from the API value.) Tj
T*
(- It shifts by the browser timezone offset.) Tj
T*
(- It returns a string trimmed to minutes so the datetime-local input can display it.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this matters for data:) Tj
T*
(- Without conversion, the saved timestamp may display incorrectly when a journal is) Tj
T*
(  reopened.) Tj
T*
(- This function is about display formatting, not database persistence.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(toIsoStringFromLocalInput\(dateValue\) in page.html line 144) Tj
T*
(Why it exists:) Tj
T*
(- HTML datetime-local gives a local date and time with no timezone marker.) Tj
T*
(- APIs and backends are usually happier with a standard ISO 8601 timestamp.) Tj
T*
(- If the user leaves the field blank, you wanted the current date and time to be sent.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How it works:) Tj
T*
(- If the field is empty, it returns new Date\(\).toISOString\(\).) Tj
T*
(- If the field has a value, it creates a Date object from that local value.) Tj
T*
(- It then returns date.toISOString\(\), which produces UTC-based ISO text.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this matters for data:) Tj
T*
(- It standardizes the payload before it leaves the browser.) Tj
T*
(- Django REST Framework can parse ISO datetimes cleanly.) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
