(- This reduces ambiguity between browser-local time and server time.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Important note:) Tj
T*
(- toISOString\(\) always produces UTC with a trailing Z.) Tj
T*
(- That means the stored value may look different from the local clock string, but it still) Tj
T*
(  represents the same moment in time.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(resetEditor\(\) in page.html line 157) Tj
T*
(Why it exists:) Tj
T*
(- The app needs a clean state when the user starts a new journal.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How it works:) Tj
T*
(- selectedJournalId becomes null.) Tj
T*
(- The title and date inputs are cleared.) Tj
T*
(- Quill content is reset.) Tj
T*
(- Focus moves back into the editor.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this matters for data:) Tj
T*
(- It prevents accidental reuse of the previous journal values.) Tj
T*
(- It makes the UI state match the user's intention to create a fresh entry.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(renderJournalList\(journals\) in page.html line 165) Tj
T*
(Why it exists:) Tj
T*
(- The API returns data objects, but users need clickable UI.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How it works:) Tj
T*
(- It maps each journal object into sidebar HTML.) Tj
T*
(- It attaches click listeners to open buttons.) Tj
T*
(- It attaches click listeners to delete buttons.) Tj
T*
(- On open, it copies the selected journal data into the title, date, and editor fields.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this matters for data:) Tj
T*
(- It is the bridge from JSON response data back into visible UI state.) Tj
T*
(- It also keeps selectedJournalId so the page knows which journal is being viewed.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(loadJournals\(searchValue = ''\) in page.html line 205) Tj
T*
(Why it exists:) Tj
T*
(- The page should load journals when it opens and refresh the list after saves or deletes.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How it works:) Tj
T*
(- It builds the URL.) Tj
T*
(- If there is search text, it adds ?search=...) Tj
T*
(- It uses fetch\(\) to request the journals list.) Tj
T*
(- It converts the response with response.json\(\).) Tj
T*
(- It hands the parsed array to renderJournalList\(\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this matters for data:) Tj
T*
(- It is the read path from Django to the browser.) Tj
T*
(- This is where the app asks the server for the current user's data.) Tj
T*
() Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
