(deleteJournal\(journalId\) in page.html line 226) Tj
T*
(Why it exists:) Tj
T*
(- Users need a way to remove saved journals.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How it works:) Tj
T*
(- It asks for confirmation.) Tj
T*
(- It sends a DELETE request to /api/journals/<id>/.) Tj
T*
(- If the deleted item is currently open, it clears the editor.) Tj
T*
(- It reloads the list.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this matters for data:) Tj
T*
(- It is a write operation against the backend.) Tj
T*
(- The frontend asks; Django actually performs the deletion.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(saveData\(\) in page.html line 254) Tj
T*
(Why it exists:) Tj
T*
(- This is the main save pipeline.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How it works:) Tj
T*
(- Reads title from #journal_title.) Tj
T*
(- Reads date from #journal_date.) Tj
T*
(- Reads HTML content from quill.root.innerHTML.) Tj
T*
(- Validates that title is not empty.) Tj
T*
(- Builds a plain JavaScript object.) Tj
T*
(- Converts it into JSON with JSON.stringify\(\).) Tj
T*
(- Sends it to /api/journals/ using fetch\(\).) Tj
T*
(- Parses the response JSON.) Tj
T*
(- Reloads the sidebar list after success.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this matters for data:) Tj
T*
(- It is the central handoff point from browser state to server persistence.) Tj
T*
(- It decides what exact payload is sent.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The payload shape is essentially:) Tj
T*
({) Tj
T*
(  "journal_title": "...",) Tj
T*
(  "journal_description": "<p>...</p>",) Tj
T*
(  "journal_date": "2026-04-08T09:30:00.000Z") Tj
T*
(}) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(searchInput.addEventListener\('input', ...\) in page.html line 295) Tj
T*
(Why it exists:) Tj
T*
(- Search should feel live instead of requiring a submit button.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How it works:) Tj
T*
(- Every time the input changes, loadJournals\(\) is called with the current text.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this matters for data:) Tj
T*
(- It changes which subset of server data is requested and displayed.) Tj
T*
() Tj
ET
endstream
