(createEntryButton.addEventListener\('click', resetEditor\) in page.html line 299) Tj
T*
(Why it exists:) Tj
T*
(- Clicking the plus button should start a new entry immediately.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How it works:) Tj
T*
(- It attaches the click event directly to the button.) Tj
T*
(- When clicked, resetEditor\(\) runs.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this matters for data:) Tj
T*
(- It changes frontend state only.) Tj
T*
(- It does not save until saveData\(\) sends a request.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. How the data should ideally be handled) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Good separation looks like this:) Tj
T*
(- Frontend responsibility: collect input, present UI, send requests, render responses.) Tj
T*
(- Serializer responsibility: validate and normalize incoming data.) Tj
T*
(- Model responsibility: define the database shape and defaults.) Tj
T*
(- View responsibility: connect request, serializer, permissions, and queryset filtering.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(That is the reason your current stack is reasonable:) Tj
T*
(- JavaScript should not write to SQLite or PostgreSQL directly.) Tj
T*
(- Django should stay responsible for database writes.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5. Why I changed the date handling the way I did) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Earlier, the model used auto_now_add or a server-side always-now behavior. That caused) Tj
T*
(user-selected dates to be ignored.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The improved idea is:) Tj
T*
(- If the frontend sends a date, keep it.) Tj
T*
(- If the frontend sends nothing, fall back to now.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This is cleaner because:) Tj
T*
(- the user can intentionally choose a journal date,) Tj
T*
(- empty input still works,) Tj
T*
(- the serializer can parse ISO 8601 cleanly,) Tj
T*
(- the model keeps a safe default.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This is also close to real-world practice:) Tj
T*
(- clients send structured values,) Tj
T*
(- servers validate them,) Tj
T*
(- servers apply defaults if fields are missing.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(6. Design notes and tradeoffs) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why use fetch\(\)?) Tj
T*
(- It is the built-in browser API for HTTP requests.) Tj
T*
(- It keeps the frontend lightweight.) Tj
T*
() Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
