(Why use response.json\(\)?) Tj
T*
(- The API returns JSON.) Tj
T*
(- The browser must parse that response text into JavaScript values before the page can use) Tj
T*
(  it.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why use addEventListener\(\)?) Tj
T*
(- It keeps behavior attached to events clearly.) Tj
T*
(- It is more flexible than old inline event patterns.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why use helper functions instead of doing everything inside saveData\(\)?) Tj
T*
(- Smaller functions are easier to debug.) Tj
T*
(- Date formatting logic can be reused.) Tj
T*
(- The code becomes easier to reason about.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(7. Things to improve next in this app) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Good next improvements:) Tj
T*
(- Use PUT or PATCH when editing an existing journal instead of always POSTing a new one.) Tj
T*
(- Store Quill Delta as well if you need richer editor history.) Tj
T*
(- Show created_at and updated_at separately from the user-chosen journal date.) Tj
T*
(- Add better error messages under form fields instead of only alert\(\).) Tj
T*
(- Convert the inline script into a separate static JavaScript file for maintainability.) Tj
T*
(- Add debouncing to search so it does not fetch on every single keystroke immediately.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(8. Learning roadmap) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Learn in this order:) Tj
T*
(1\) JavaScript basics: objects, functions, arrays, events.) Tj
T*
(2\) The DOM: query selectors, input values, innerHTML, event listeners.) Tj
T*
(3\) HTTP basics: GET, POST, DELETE, headers, status codes.) Tj
T*
(4\) JSON: stringify and parse.) Tj
T*
(5\) Dates and timezones: local time, UTC, ISO 8601.) Tj
T*
(6\) Django REST Framework serializers and viewsets.) Tj
T*
(7\) Authentication, sessions, and CSRF.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(9. Small projects to build) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Project 1: Notes app) Tj
T*
(- Title and body fields.) Tj
T*
(- Save notes with fetch\(\).) Tj
T*
(- List notes from the backend.) Tj
T*
(- Delete notes.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Project 2: Task manager) Tj
T*
(- Task text, due date, completed flag.) Tj
T*
(- Filter by completed or pending.) Tj
T*
(- Practice JSON payloads and form handling.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Project 3: Expense tracker) Tj
T*
(- Amount, category, note, datetime.) Tj
ET
